# Executive Governance for SAP Implementation

> Business Intelligence Case Study

---

## Overview

During the SAP implementation project, executive monitoring depended on manual consolidation of Microsoft Project files into PowerPoint presentations.

The process was time-consuming, repetitive and provided limited visibility into project performance.

To address this challenge, I developed a Business Intelligence solution that automated data collection, centralized project information and delivered executive dashboards for PMOs, GMOs, managers and directors.

---

## Business Challenge

The project involved multiple workstreams, suppliers and hundreds of tasks running simultaneously.

Project monitoring relied on:

- Microsoft Project
- Excel spreadsheets
- Manual PowerPoint reports

As a result:

- Updates consumed several hours every week
- Historical information was difficult to maintain
- Executive reporting depended on manual work
- Decision-making was slower than required

---

## Solution

The solution consisted of building an analytical platform capable of transforming operational project data into executive information.

Main components:

- Automated extraction of Microsoft Project files
- Historical database generation
- Automatic backup process
- Data modeling
- Executive dashboards in Power BI
- Interactive project monitoring

---

## My Responsibilities

- Business requirements gathering
- Dashboard design
- Data modeling
- Power BI development
- Python automation
- Documentation
- Continuous improvements throughout the implementation

